--- body ---
## Epic goal
`scripts/` holds 173 flat files that are really a **library plus a set of entry
points**. Group the pure entry points by dataflow phase so the directory names
the phase — WITHOUT a top-level `src/`, without a `python -m` flip, and without
churning the ~160 `from utils import` / ~93 `script_io_args` call sites. This is
the high-risk stage of the code reorg (sub-tracker `0225`, grand-tracker `0223`);
it is decomposed here into de-risked, independently-landable children.

## The two-tier rule (baked in — do not re-open)
Two tiers move differently:
- **Tier-3 — pure entry points** (run, never imported): move into
  `scripts/<phase>/` (`figures/`, `harvest/`, `analysis/`, `qa/`).
- **Tier-2 — internal library modules** (imported by another script — `utils`,
  `pipeline_*`, `schemas`, `script_io_args`, `_*`-private, and any helper only
  ever imported): STAY FLAT at `scripts/` root. That flat root becomes the
  library surface on the path.
A file that is BOTH an entry point AND imported is resolved by the 0254 audit:
either its library part is extracted into a neutral flat `_*` module (the 0250
pattern), or it is reclassified Tier-2. `libs/<pkg>` (cross-project,
`openalex-corpus`) is a SEPARATE track (ticket 0229, AEDIST-gated) — NOT part of
this epic.

## Approved import-path model (decisions 1+2, do not re-open)
Unify the repo on **relative source roots** (filed as 0253):
- `pytest` `pythonpath = ["scripts", "libs/openalex-corpus/src"]` +
  Makefile `PYTHONPATH=scripts:libs/openalex-corpus/src`.
- This RETIRES the `tests/conftest.py` `sys.path.insert` hack AND the
  non-editable `openalex-corpus` `[tool.uv.sources]` local install, while KEEPING
  `libs/openalex-corpus/pyproject.toml` (AEDIST consumes it by git source, 0229).
- **De-shim**: drop the pure re-export pass-throughs (`pipeline_text` re-exporting
  `normalize_doi` / `reconstruct_abstract`), but KEEP `pipeline_io.retry_get` (a
  real adapter injecting `MAILTO`).
Flat module names stay (`from utils import`) — zero import churn; no `src/`, no
`python -m`.

The tables-vs-intermediate-output split stays at the ARTIFACT layer
(`deliverables/_shared/tables/` vs `data/derived/`, already guarded) — it does
NOT drive script grouping.

## Wave structure
- **Wave 0** (foundations, parallel, no prerequisite):
  - 0b — import-path model (0253). Load-bearing: unblocks every move.
  - 0a — entry-point/library classification audit + extract embedded helpers
    (0254). Produces the definitive Tier-2/Tier-3 list.
- **Wave 1** (the moves, each Blocked-by 0253 + 0254; independent of each other):
  0255 figures, 0256 harvest, 0257 analysis, 0258 qa.
- **Wave 2** (extractions): 0241 lands the five SPLIT extractions in the phase
  subdirs — Blocked-by 0257 (the analysis move that creates the destination).
- **Independent**: 0259 restores the seed-scan coverage 0250 narrowed.

Already done (closed): 0242 (sever clustering back-arrow), 0248 (unify .mk
discovery), 0250 (wave-0a exemplar — extracted `build_pre2007_traditions` to
neutral `scripts/_pre2007_traditions.py`).

## Children checklist (tracker closes when all are closed)
- [ ] 0253 — wave-0b: import-path model (source roots + retire conftest hack +
      retire non-editable wheel + de-shim). Blocked-by: none.
- [ ] 0254 — wave-0a: entry-point/library classification audit + extract embedded
      helpers; publishes the Tier-2/Tier-3 list. Blocked-by: none.
- [ ] 0255 — wave-1: move `scripts/figures/` (`plot_*`/`export_*`). Blocked-by: 0253 0254.
- [ ] 0256 — wave-1: move `scripts/harvest/` (`catalog_/enrich_/corpus_/scout*`). Blocked-by: 0253 0254.
- [ ] 0257 — wave-1: move `scripts/analysis/` (`analyze_/compute_/summarize_/build_het_core`). Blocked-by: 0253 0254.
- [ ] 0258 — wave-1: move `scripts/qa/` (`qa_*`). Blocked-by: 0253 0254.
- [ ] 0241 — wave-2: land the five SPLIT extractions in their phase subdir. Blocked-by: 0257.
- [ ] 0259 — hygiene: `RANDOM_STATE` → `config/analysis.yaml`. Blocked-by: none.

## Invariants (inherited by every child)
- No top-level `src/`; no `python -m` flip; flat module names unchanged.
- Only Tier-3 entry points move; Tier-2 library modules stay flat.
- Layering (architecture.md rule 4): a compute module never imports a plotter.
- `make check` green; `make clean && make all` green.
- One logical move per PR.

## Exit criteria (tracker closes when)
- 0253, 0254, 0255, 0256, 0257, 0258, 0241, 0259 all closed.
- `scripts/` grouped by phase; no flat ~170-file directory; Tier-2 library surface
  intact at `scripts/` root.
- `make -n` target lists unchanged by the moves; full build green.

